text.text:

text.text:
Fantastic cocktail bar in St. Pauli! The chug concept is super creative ‚Äì small, flavorful tequila and mezcal cocktails that let you try different tastes without overdoing it - The bartender is a true master at crafting the perfect mix of drinks!

The staff are passionate and friendly, and the atmosphere is cozy. One of the best parts ‚Äî they offer free water, which feels like a real luxury after a couple of cocktails.

The only feedback I have to make the experience even better is to kindly request that guests smoke outside, since the bar is small and the smoke can get overwhelming at times for non-smokers like me.

But still hands down one of the best bars in Hamburg and a must-visit for cocktail lovers!

text.text:
It's one of the nicest bars in Hamburg. The ambient is really cool, with the deemed light and wall arts it gives an interesting vibe.
Place can be a little darker shade but feels good. Definitely gets full, and it is a small place.
One of the fewest places that serves "Herrengedeck."
Herrengedeck is a combo with beer of choice that comes with a schnap, bread, and pickles on the side.
They got really good beers on the tap, and the cocktails are also well prepared.
The staff is very friendly and they also speak english.
The only thing I miss is I wish they would also serve fries with the beers. But no. Nevertheless, that does not change my eagerness to go there.

editorialSummary.text: 20th floor bar in the Empire Riverside Hotel with panoramic views & floor-to-ceiling windows.

text.text:
The view- amazing! It makes sense to visit here if you are in Hamburg. Just try to reserve in advance!
I went there with a friend, and got to witness a beautiful sunset over the city and the docks.

The cocktails are absolutely delightful, I just wish they also had some finger snacks to order.

We ordered two drinks each and sat there for almost 3 hours. Dancing chili is a trendsetter here but I honestly loved the Mai Tai wayyy more. The gin basil smash was brilliantly fresh too.

text.text:
A lovely and unique bar near the Elbe River in Hamburg.
Having watched Channel 4's "Travelman" series of programmes, this was too good an opportunity to miss.
Service was impeccable, and we sat outside as it was still warm in the first week of September. We were provided with glasses of water and sweet popcorn and then perused the cocktail menu.  This place drips their alcohol over foods to imbue them with the flavour - salted peanut, for example.  The enhanced alcohols are then used in bespoke and unique cocktails for the customer's pleasure. I additionally had a pint of Pilsner lager to cleanse my palate and slake my thirst.
Highly recommended, quiet, discrete, exceptionally good value and easy to reach on foot being just off the Reeperbahn.

We were here on 16-11-2024. Very relaxed atmosphere, not specifically a cocktail bar vibe, but the atmosphere has something, very pleasant. We had the Enigma, Dinner in Yokohama, Reporn, Madame Le and Sams no 1.
Good cocktails, without a doubt. Creative? "Jein"....See it as music, people here often do not compose themselves but mainly make covers. Like this example. Take a cocktail like the Espresso Martini as a starting point, tweak it a bit and voila the "Dinner in Yokohama" is born.
Would we come back here? Absolutely. Only downside...few rum drinks on the menu.

Turm Cocktailbar in Hamburg offers a standout experience for cocktail lovers. I tried the Peach Punch and the Lillet Cherry Berry‚Äîboth were exceptionally well-crafted, balanced in flavor, and beautifully presented. The bartenders clearly know their craft, and the quality of ingredients shines through in every sip.

The atmosphere is another highlight: stylish, vibrant, and with a unique character that sets it apart from the usual bar scene. It‚Äôs a place that invites you to stay a little longer, enjoy the mood, and discover new favorites from the menu.

A solid 4-star experience‚Äîexcellent drinks and an engaging ambiance. Just a touch more refinement in service or seating comfort could push it into 5-star territory. Still, highly recommended for a night out in Hamburg.

text.text:
Turm Cocktailbar in Hamburg offers a standout experience for cocktail lovers. I tried the Peach Punch and the Lillet Cherry Berry‚Äîboth were exceptionally well-crafted, balanced in flavor, and beautifully presented. The bartenders clearly know their craft, and the quality of ingredients shines through in every sip.

The atmosphere is another highlight: stylish, vibrant, and with a unique character that sets it apart from the usual bar scene. It‚Äôs a place that invites you to stay a little longer, enjoy the mood, and discover new favorites from the menu.

A solid 4-star experience‚Äîexcellent drinks and an engaging ambiance. Just a touch more refinement in service or seating comfort could push it into 5-star territory. Still, highly recommended for a night out in Hamburg.
